            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What you can find in this playlist            </h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-6">
            Genres spreading across borders in the ’60s: <br/>
<!-- Subsections -->
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">    <span class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Ska:</span> fast, horn-driven, and politically cheeky; the soundtrack of Jamaica’s independence. Super popular in UK

</div>
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
<span class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Calypso:</span> carnival music with gossip, humor, and satire at its core. Almost 100 year old sound that is one of the most influential genres in the western world
</div>
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
<span class="font-bold text-[#06161]">Rocksteady:</span> ska slowed down, more soulful and bass-heavy (a direct precursor to reggae and Dancehall).
</div>
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
<span class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Compas:</span> Haiti’s most danceable export, smoothing méringue into modern electric grooves.
</div>
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
<span class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Bolero & Son:</span> big across Cuba, Puerto Rico, and the Spanish-speaking Caribbean.
</div>
<div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
<span class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Salsa (early form):</span> brewing in New York via Puerto Rican and Cuban diasporas, heavily influenced by the island scenes.
</div>


          </div>

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- The Tech Factor -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.75 17L9 20l-1 1h8l-1-1-.75-3M3 13h18M5 17h14a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Technological changes </h4>
          </div>
